description: Numbers n such that n remains prime through 5 iterations of function f(x) = 4x + 9.
comments: n, 4*n+9, 16*n+45, 64*n+189, 256*n+765 and 1024*n+3069 are primes. [From _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 05 2010]
prog: (MAGMA) [n: n in [1..10000000] | IsPrime(n) and IsPrime(4*n+9) and IsPrime(16*n+45) and IsPrime(64*n+189) and IsPrime(256*n+765) and IsPrime(1024*n+3069)] [From _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 05 2010]
author: _David W. Wilson_
